.Sh INTERFACE STABILITY
The command line interface of
.Nm
is
.Sy Committed .
.Sh NOTES
.Ss XPG4 ksh93
Uses arithmetic expressions such as
.Bd -literal -offset Ds
$(( x > 3.1 ))
.Ed
.Pp
instead of
.Bd -literal -offset Ds
$ /usr/bin/test "$x" -gt 3.1
.Ed
.Pp
when comparing two floating-point variables or a constant and a floating-point
variable to prevent rounding errors (caused by the base16 to base10
transformation) to affect the result.
Additionally the built-in arithmetic
support in XPG4
.Sy ksh93
is significantly faster because it does not require the explicit transformation
to strings for each comparison.
